column2:
The early death of an immediate family member from a heart attack is a warning sign that you are at a higher risk of having one. 
Taking the following actions can decrease your risk: 
(1) reduce fat intake in your diet; 
(2) stop smoking; 
(3) seek treatment if you have high blood pressure; 
(4) exercise regularly; 
(5) adjust your lifestyle to reduce stress; 
(6) diet with the advice of a dietitian if you are overweight; and 
(7) see your doctor for cardiac risk factor screening.
